@startuml
title Viaverse Analytics / Observability — Class Model

class ProductEvent {
  id: UUID
  eventName: String
  schemaVersion: Int
  anonymousId: String?
  accountIdHash: String?
  sessionId: String
  properties: Json
  sensitivity: Sensitivity
  occurredAt: Instant
}

class EventSchema {
  eventName: String
  version: Int
  ownerTeam: String
  requiredFields: Set<String>
  retentionClass: RetentionClass
  status: ACTIVE | DEPRECATED
}

class AnalyticsConsent {
  accountId: AccountId?
  anonymousId: String
  analyticsEnabled: Boolean
  marketingEnabled: Boolean
  updatedAt: Instant
}

class ServiceMetric {
  name: String
  service: String
  tags: Map<String,String>
  value: Decimal
  timestamp: Instant
  sloName: String?
}

class TraceContext {
  traceId: String
  spanId: String
  correlationId: String
  serviceName: String
  operationName: String
  sampled: Boolean
}

class StructuredLog {
  timestamp: Instant
  level: LogLevel
  service: String
  message: String
  traceId: String?
  correlationId: String?
  redactionStatus: RedactionStatus
}

class AlertRule {
  id: UUID
  name: String
  source: METRIC | LOG | TRACE
  condition: String
  severity: Severity
  runbookUrl: String
  enabled: Boolean
}

class ObservabilityEvents {
  ProductEventIngested
  SchemaValidationFailed
  SloBreached
  AlertRaised
  RetentionApplied
}

ProductEvent --> EventSchema : validated by
AnalyticsConsent ..> ProductEvent : controls
ServiceMetric --> AlertRule : triggers
TraceContext --> StructuredLog : correlates
TraceContext ..> ServiceMetric : exemplars
StructuredLog --> AlertRule : triggers
ProductEvent ..> ObservabilityEvents : emits
EventSchema ..> ObservabilityEvents : validation failures
AlertRule ..> ObservabilityEvents : emits

note bottom
Analytics properties must be allowlisted by schema.
Free-form client payloads are not accepted into trusted metrics.
end note
@enduml
